description.narrative: (Tanzania): With FY 2020 funds, D4D will provide services to support USAID/Tanzania to improve data-driven decision-making, planning, and implementation for implementing partners (IPs), and strategic local partners, including GOT policymakers. This activity will build USAID/Tanzania's capacity to monitor and evaluate activities by conducting ten evaluations and assessments, fifty data quality assessments, and training courses for USAID/Tanzania and partners. This activity will transfer knowledge to USAID/Tanzania staff during implementation and provide on-the-job training to ensure that skills are transferred to relevant staff to support the sustainability of the activity. With FY 2020 funds, this activity will have a particular emphasis on improving the capacity of USAID/Tanzania staff to improve activity monitoring. This activity contributes to the U.S. Government's priority to maximize investments in Tanzania by continuously learning from ongoing and ending activities and applying lessons. ..&amp;amp;lt;!--td {border: 1px solid #ccc;}br {mso-data-placement:same-cell;}--&amp;amp;gt;
